         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>354</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">being in the power of the wish ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... they praised the Buddhalord, the teacher in that way ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the jewel consisting in hearing the speech of the sūtra ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>249</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... you (sg.) have become an island of jewels ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... the desire towards the goodness in hearing the Law ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... from all sufferings (they are freed) by you, oh venerable one ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... he went to the ... . Then ... this divine ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (without) hesitation he says: In [the tune] viśikkoṃ:</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (if) Vaiśravaṇa has come, ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... (if) Dhṛdhirāṣṭra has come ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... in order to see the community of monks. If ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... having adorned the riding animal of (Ga)ruḍa ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="remarks">Left part of a leaf with part of the string hole space preserved in lines 3 and 4. The leaf number 35 is repeated inside the string hole space on the verso side. Unlike in other cases in this mansucript, the number written inside the string hole does not deviate from the one written on the margin. This is true for the continuous series <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a32"/> until <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-a36"/>.</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment"><hi>viśikkoṃ</hi>: a metre of 4 x 18 syllables (7|7|4).</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">The line probably begins with the 2nd syllable of pāda 1b.</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">The line probably begins with the 9th syllable of pāda 1c.</note></p>
         </div>
